    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.2.6" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Cylinder Heads</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, mount cylinder head lifting bracket on center of cylinder
                    head. Also, make sure the lifting hook has a safety latch.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3450010030" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cylinder Head Lifting Bracket ZTSE4535</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder Head Lifting Bracket ZTSE4535</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lifting bracket mounting bolt (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The lifting bracket allows each cylinder head to be removed squarely from the crankcase.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">Cylinder Head Lifting Bracket ZTSE4535</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>
                on cylinder head over the center two cylinders, install and tighten four lifting bracket mounting bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a lifting hoist hook or suitable lifting sling to lifting bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010031" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08124.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Cylinder head bolts (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 70 bolt (5)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder head bolt (10)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a circular pattern loosen, remove, and discard ten cylinder head bolts. Begin with the
                outer bolts and move inward.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove five M8 x 70 bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift cylinder head from crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not scratch gasket surface of cylinder head.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place cylinder head on a protected surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard cylinder head gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010032" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08143.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Cylinder head spring dowel pins in crankcase (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two spring dowel pins.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For left cylinder head, remove two flat countersunk screws and lifting eye.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For right cylinder head, remove two M10 x 25 bolts and lifting eye.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
